HEADWORD: Gladen
<hw>Gla"den</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>gl⟦ae⟧dene</ets>, cf. L. <ets>gladius</ets> a sword. Cf.
<er>Gladiole</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Sword grass; any plant
with sword-shaped leaves, especially the European <spn>Iris
f⟦oe⟧tidissima</spn>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>gladwyn</asp>,
<asp>gladdon</asp>, and <asp>glader</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

